<span class="math">$\\pi&#x27; = PK(\\mu_1, \\mu_2, \\rho_1, \\rho_2, \\rho_3 : E_t = \\mathsf{Enc}_{\\mathsf{pkt}}(g^{\\mu_1}; \\rho_1) \\land C_v = \\mathsf{Com}_h(g^{\\mu_2}; \\rho_3) \\land E_m = \\mathsf{Enc}_{\\mathsf{pkm}}(g^{\\mu_1 \\mu_2}; \\rho_2)) ,</span>$
